<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-06T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10–3144:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-07T00:00:00-04:00">November
                                    7, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9326. From Department and FEA. Bern’s 7245, October 31 to Department. In
                            the event of an unsatisfactory reply (foreshadowed by Pilet-Golaz
                            remarks) by the Swiss Federal Council to our <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> of October 31 [<hi rend="italic">30?</hi>], we feel
                            formal withdrawal to our joint offer of supplies should be made without
                            delay in order to protect our future position.</p>
                        <p>You are requested to approach MEW at once to ascertain their views.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Bern as Department’s 3787. [Department and FEA.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>